Hello everyone! 
I also decided to speak out, having thought a little about what was happening in the chat... 

First of all, I will note the guys who really tried and did something. There were many worthy creators here, if you do not count all the passers-by who tried to bypass the system with the help of AI. You are cool!

As for the organization, I would like to note a few things: 
1. Thank you for the opportunity to give people a chance to speak out, there are few such â€œchallengesâ€ in this area. 
2. It was great to see different interpretations of the same words by different people, including in their own style! 
3. I even managed to meet and talk to someone, which is also great.

But there are things to consider to avoid future disputes if you plan to interact further with the authors or community. This is the preparation of the technical task... 

When you write:
Â«Weâ€™re launching an open design contest â€” and looking for 3 epic logos.
Thereâ€™s no brief. No rules. Just pure creativity.Â» & Â«Weâ€™re not after something â€œsafe.â€ We want bold, meaningful visuals that speak for themselves.Â»

This means that people will try to immerse themselves in creativity as much as possible, to show their vision and what they are capable of!

After such a technical task, you throw into the chat 3 icons that you have already chosen... and in the end the winners (I have no questions for them: the most resourceful one wins) are those people who made minimal changes to your wishes... For this, it was possible not to hold a competition and save $3000 ğŸ˜…

It's just that other guys spent a lot of their time (luckily, this is one of the winners) and some stars... This is a strange attitude towards guys in a field in which the final product is the activity of creators...ğŸ™„

Pick at least a few of them and give them a tamagotchi ğŸ˜… or pick the concepts you like the most and pin them in the chat, maybe someone will notice them and give them work in other projects) There is no need for this anymore, I'm just suggesting how to smooth things out)

I think this was the first experience of such interaction with the audience, and I hope that in the future this will be taken into account so that there are no disagreements between the community and the organizers! After all, such events always have a positive effect on the development of the community.

Anyway, thanks to everyone for the contestâ€¦ both the participants and the organizers! Good luck to everyone! It was an interesting experience. Peace ğŸ€
